<item>
            <title>[JDK-8307067] remove broken EnableThreadSMRExtraValidityChecks option</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8307067</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>The EnableThreadSMRExtraValidityChecks diagnostic option&lt;br/&gt;
is broken and should be removed.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
If -XX:-EnableThreadSMRExtraValidityChecks is specified the&lt;br/&gt;
ThreadsListHandle::cv_internal_thread_to_JavaThread() function&lt;br/&gt;
can return an unprotected JavaThread* and use of that JavaThread*&lt;br/&gt;
can result in crashes.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This was discussed during the reviews for the following fix:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8305670&quot; title=&quot;Performance regression in LockSupport.unpark with lots of idle threads&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8305670&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8305670&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Performance regression in LockSupport.unpark with lots of idle threads </description>
